AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 502* House Bill No. 658
by deleting SECTION 7 and substituting:
SECTION 7. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 63, Chapter 24, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
An out-of-state applicant from a state not having a current licensure or
certification act or an expired license or certificate in good standing at the time of
expiration will be eligible to take the jurisprudence examination if certified by the board of
certification and approved by the commissioner.
SECTION 8. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 63, Chapter 24, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
An applicant is entitled to an athletic trainer's license if the applicant:
(1) Possesses the requirements enumerated in § 63-24-104;
(2) Completes and passes the certification requirements and examination
of the board of certification or its equivalent as determined by the commissioner;
(3) Completes the jurisprudence examination administered and selected
by the commissioner, to the commissioner's satisfaction;
(4) Pays the licensure fee as determined by the commissioner; and
(5) Has not committed an act that constitutes grounds for denial of a
license under § 63-24-107.
SECTION 9.
